All done. Here's a summary of what was built:

**Source files:**
- `src/pricing.ts` — Item values, base premiums, component block pricing
- `src/quote.ts` — Premium computation with all modifiers (cursed, enchantment, loyalty, first insurance, follow-up, processing fee)
- `src/claim.ts` — Claim processing with deductible, enchantment reimbursement reduction, cap enforcement, and rounding
- `src/engine.ts` — Scenario runner that processes sequential quote/claim steps with correct step-index policy references
- `src/cli.ts` — CLI entry point reading JSON from stdin, writing results to stdout, error handling to stderr

**Test files (70 tests, all passing):**
- `src/pricing.spec.ts` — 16 tests for item values, base premiums, component block pricing
- `src/quote.spec.ts` — 16 tests for premium modifiers and integration examples
- `src/claim.spec.ts` — 17 tests for deductible, enchantment/dragon clauses, cap, rounding, errors
- `src/engine.spec.ts` — 21 tests including CLI subprocess tests, interleaved steps, all prompt examples
